Days: sat-mon
Where: 2hrs from my moms house https://goo.gl/maps/Dbr33YF4gCLsMtf76
Typical Schedule: 
Day 1 - drive up sat to get there early afternoon and setup, small fire, chill
Day 2 - wakeup to catch a bus to drive 10 miles up river, get in a canoe and canoe down back to our campsite. takes 3-5 hrs. we stop on little islands for lunch. you see the occasional eagles and stuff. depending on the water level there will be some rapids.
Go back and chill. usually have a large bonfire in the middle (where my fire jumping pics were taken)
Day 3 - breakfast, can explore more, packup and leave

We reserve a parking spot for our camp ground. it can fit 2 cars, has garbage cans and a water faucet. Then there are 2 bathroom/shower facilities there in the middle of the field. my sister said they're going to have some type of COVID guidelines for that.

There's a camp store with your basics at the entrance. thats also where we check in.
We usually buy firewood from the locals. fill a pickup bed.
